# Server API Conventions

See `architecture-backend.mdc` for full backend architecture. Quick reference:

## Routes
- File: `backend/src/routes/*Routes.ts`; export `*Router`
- Thin handlers: validate → call service → `sendSuccess` / `handleRouteError`
- SQL belongs in `backend/src/services/`, not route files

## Auth & Tenant
- Mount with `authMiddleware` + `requireActiveSubscription()` in `backend/src/index.ts`
- `req.tenantId`, `req.userId`, `req.role` on `AuthedRequest` after auth
- RBAC: `requirePermission('feature.action')` or mount-level `requirePermissionWhenPathStartsWith`
- Admin portal: `backend/src/adminPortal/` with `adminAuthMiddleware`

## Errors
- Validate input; `sendFailure(res, 400, 'message')` for bad requests
- Rate limiting on public endpoints (login, lookup)
- Log with `console.error`; never expose internals to client
